--- !u!114 &1318753246
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1318753244}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5ad1d7fb7f6172a45b05986fb296a635, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: '::'
  dialogueText: {fileID: 1461506044}
  dialogueLines:
  - Welcome to the login page!
  - First, try any value you think is correct
  - 'Now try \n<color=red>admin'' --</color> in the username field '
  - See how the rest of the query becomes a comment
  - 'Now click the login button to enter '
  - Good job
  - but what if you dont have any username?
  - Easy!
  - ' try <color=red>'' OR 1=1 --</color>'
  - Because 1=1 is always true
  - Good job soldier!
  - You can also <color=#B83D00>Inject Malicious SQL</color>!
  - use <color=#B83D00>name');DELETE FROM users;</color>
  - Username is wrong? the DELETE query will still run!
  - Nice work
  - Now complete all your missions!
  - Ahha! You found me again
  - 'as you can see the url is in the root path '
  - did you know we can access other page by changing the url?
  - 'This is called \n <color=red>Broken Access Control</color> '
  - Now, open your Linux terminal soldier
  - 'we can use <color=#26D4AE>gobuster</color> to directory brute force '
  - 'First, we can enter the url of the website '
  - 'Copy <color=#E8AA31>http://bank.com</color> from the website '
  - Now go paste it in the terminal url field
  - 'Good job! '
  - Now we need a list of common file paths
  - ' lets go to Files'
  - press <color=#26D4AE>CTRL SHIFT F</color> to search
  - type in <color=#26D4AE>common.txt</color> and hit ENTER
  - copy the file path, paste it in the terminal
  - Now hit enter
  - It now shows all the hidden url that we can access
  - head to the firefox
  - 'Try out <color=#26D4AE>http://bank.com/admin.php</color> and hit ENTER '
  - Boom we discovered hidden pages
  - Now complete your Missions!
  - How did you know Im here?
  - This is a feedback form of the Bank
  - We can inject malicious scripts into any input fields
  - try <color=#7733ff><script>alert("NAME")</script></color>
  - 'Now click Submit '
  - Nice! See how your alert is triggered?
  - But there is a more <color=red>harmful</color> method
  - First, go to the terminal
  - type\n<color=#3333ff>sudo beef-xss</color> hit ENTER
  - We have successfully launch beEF!
  - 'Now, copy the <color=#b30000>Example script</color> '
  - paste it in the feedback form input
  - Lets go to the beEF control panel
  - Currently there are no online browsers
  - but when other device logs in....
  - Boom the user is now tracked
  - First, click on the user
  - go to commands
  - Click on  <color=#26D4AE>Social Engineering</color>
  - click google phishing and EXCECUTE
  - Look, the user browser will display the fake page
  - 'you are able to see all their input in the Logs '
  - Now complete all your Missions
  - Glad you found the three!
  - This is the bank transfer page
  - We can trick it to excecute transfers
  - when the victim is logged in their browser
  - This is called <color=#009900>Cross Site Request Forgery</color>
  - First, lets inspect the form
  - Press the "I" key to inpsect
  - Now, open the form
  - We can see all the variables needed by the form
  - Double click them to copy when needed
  - Now head to the terminal
  - We need to create a fake request with html
  - Copy and paste the bank link
  - Great! Variable 1 is <color=#258e8e>account_number\n_from</color>
  - 'Variable 2 will be our account <color=#258e8e>account_number\n_to</color> '
  - Next <color=#258e8e>amount=100000</color> in the 3rd variable
  - input the filename as <color=#258e8e>index.html</color>
  - Hit Enter
  - 'Nice! We need to copy the file to the server location '
  - To copy the file,<color=#258e8e>cp index.html</color>
  - location is <color=#258e8e>/var/www/html/index.html</color>
  - Hit Enter
  - 'Start the service <color=#258e8e>sudo systemctl start apache2</color> '
  - Nice! Hit Enter
  - Do you know how to share to the victim?
  - Use <color=#258e8e>hostname -I</color>  to know your IP address
  - Good hit Enter
  - 'Thus, the link is <color=#258e8e>http://192.168.21.129/index.html</color> '
  - Now, head to WhatsApp in Firefox
  - 'Send <color=#258e8e>http://192.168.21.129/index.html</color> '
  - 'When the victim clicks on the Hyperlink '
  - It will trigger the transaction on their end
  - Now complete all your Missions!
  - This is the final stretch!
  - Look at the paper he dropped
  - It has the premium credentials
  - Login with it!
  - Nice!
  - Now Hit "I" to inspect
  - Click storage
  - Oops, they put the JWT token here
  - Copy the value of the token
  - Now head to JWT.io site
  - Paste it in the encoded input
  - Now we can see the user structure
  - Look, the membership is "premium"
  - That means we can get premium without paying
  - Now, head to the terminal
  - Excecute <color=#00D0D9>burpsuite &</color>
  - Good, lets go to BurpSuite
  - Go to proxy
  - Turn on intercept
  - Good, now go to the bank page
  - See there is a proxy!
  - Click on it
  - Enable it for your IP address
  - Now, click "Create new account"
  - Input the username you want and register as usual
  - Enter password you want
  - Reconfirm the password you entered
  - Hit Create New Account
  - Now the request is intercepted
  - Head to the burpsuite
  - Click <color=#00D0D9>Action</color>
  - Click <color=#00D0D9>Send to Repeater</color>
  - Now head to Repeater tab
  - 'Modify the membership field to<color=#00D0D9>"membership" : "premium"</color>  '
  - 'Now hit send! '
  - 'Status: Success!'
  - Now login with your created account
  - Look! you are now a premium member!
  - Complete all your Missions
  - Talk to the NPC to get Mission every round!
  - Use the scoll bar to view!
  - Welcome to the <color=blue>Blue Team Stations!</color>
  - You must make sure the code is <color=#00e600>secure</color>
  - Read the explanation and Start when ready
  - Hold <color=blue>"Ctrl"</color> key to activate scan
  - Now modify the code until its secure!
  - Click "Patch" once done!
  typingSpeed: 0.04
  waitNextLine: 1.5
